{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01EHCnw9o6duqS3ZY3t7h6aC","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Mutations (FR-14)\n2\t\n3\tServer-only mutation framework for approved peek admin changes.\n4\t\n5\t- `registry.ts` — frozen registry keyed by stable action id; each definition declares the FR-2 action id, audit `resourceType`, zod input schema, and a transactional `execute` callback that returns the audit-friendly resource id + before/after diff.\n6\t- `runner.ts` — `runPeekMutation` orchestration: action-id lookup, role check (`isActionAllowedForRole`), input validation, `sql.begin(...)` transaction, and audit hooks (`peek.change.applied` on success, `peek.change.rejected` on unknown action / unauthorized / invalid input / execution failure / audit-emit failure). Audit insert runs on the same transactional `Sql` so the mutation and its audit record commit or roll back together.\n7\t- `index.ts` — public surface re-exporting the runner + registry types.\n8\t\n9\tThis iteration ships the framework only. Approved mutations (KOL rate, fraud-flag status, dogpile cancel, reward-config edit) land in subsequent FR-14 iterations.\n10\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fbb345f7-d650-4fa3-be65-355d8ff344be","uuid":"a5f14337-3633-42e7-bba7-ef3e9f90afd2","timestamp":"2026-04-26T20:01:45.748Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/peek/src/server/mutations/README.md","content":"# Mutations (FR-14)\n\nServer-only mutation framework for approved peek admin changes.\n\n- `registry.ts` — frozen registry keyed by stable action id; each definition declares the FR-2 action id, audit `resourceType`, zod input schema, and a transactional `execute` callback that returns the audit-friendly resource id + before/after diff.\n- `runner.ts` — `runPeekMutation` orchestration: action-id lookup, role check (`isActionAllowedForRole`), input validation, `sql.begin(...)` transaction, and audit hooks (`peek.change.applied` on success, `peek.change.rejected` on unknown action / unauthorized / invalid input / execution failure / audit-emit failure). Audit insert runs on the same transactional `Sql` so the mutation and its audit record commit or roll back together.\n- `index.ts` — public surface re-exporting the runner + registry types.\n\nThis iteration ships the framework only. Approved mutations (KOL rate, fraud-flag status, dogpile cancel, reward-config edit) land in subsequent FR-14 iterations.\n","numLines":10,"startLine":1,"totalLines":10}}}
