{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01NDKM5z7Wrneyuphd7Dwxsj","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I'll update `peek/README.md` to cover all the operations admin context required by the checklist item."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":568,"cache_read_input_tokens":90376,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":568},"output_tokens":41,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fbb345f7-d650-4fa3-be65-355d8ff344be","uuid":"0da5a82a-1257-49de-bb19-0f2c8eff6853"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01NDKM5z7Wrneyuphd7Dwxsj","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01GUftPAkAf4MpJCmqmoXo98","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/peek/README.md","content":"# Peek\n\nInternal operations admin for Taunt Bet — users, growth/referrals, games, economy (rewards/points/crates/challenges), queue, dogpile, fraud review, audit, and exports — built on Next.js App Router with server-only Postgres reads and a small set of audited admin mutations.\n\nUses **pnpm** (pinned in `package.json` `packageManager`). Non-frontend service repos in this org standardize on pnpm.\n\n## Setup\n\n```bash\npnpm install\ncp .env.example .env.local\npnpm dev\n```\n\n## Required env\n\n- `DATABASE_URL`\n- `CF_ACCESS_TEAM_DOMAIN` — Cloudflare Access team domain, e.g. `https://team.cloudflareaccess.com`\n- `CF_ACCESS_AUD` — Cloudflare Access application audience tag\n\n## Optional env\n\n- `PEEK_ACCESS_POLICY` — JSON array mapping verified Cloudflare emails/domains to local roles. See \"Local roles\" below.\n- `PEEK_DEV_ACCESS_EMAIL` — local-only Cloudflare Access bypass; honored only when `NODE_ENV=development`. See \"Local dev identity\" below.\n- `PEEK_DEFAULT_PAGE_SIZE` — defaults to `50` if unset.\n- `PEEK_DB_CONNECT_TIMEOUT_SECONDS` — defaults to `5` so the UI fails fast when the database is unreachable.\n\n## Cloudflare Access (jose)\n\nCloudflare Zero Trust Access is the outer identity gate. `peek` does **not** maintain a second global email allowlist for base access — Cloudflare decides who can reach the app.\n\nThe proxy (`peek/proxy.ts`) verifies the `cf-access-jwt-assertion` header on every request using [`jose`](https://github.com/panva/jose):\n\n- `createRemoteJWKSet(${CF_ACCESS_TEAM_DOMAIN}/cdn-cgi/access/certs)` fetches and caches the signing keys.\n- `jwtVerify(...)` validates signature, `algorithms: [\"RS256\"]`, `issuer = CF_ACCESS_TEAM_DOMAIN`, `audience = CF_ACCESS_AUD`, and expiration.\n- The verified `email` claim is normalized (trimmed + lowercased), then forwarded as the trusted server-only `x-peek-verified-access-email` header. Any browser-supplied copy of that header is stripped before any downstream code runs.\n- A request without a valid JWT receives `403 Cloudflare Access required`. A request with a valid JWT but missing `email` claim is denied at render time by the role resolver (no role → access-denied panel).\n\nCustom JWKS / signature code has been removed; production correctness depends on `jose`'s validation.\n\n## Local roles (FR-2)\n\nA valid Cloudflare JWT proves identity. App authorization is decided locally in `peek/src/server/access-policy.ts`, keyed off the verified email.\n\nRoles: `business` and `admin`. `admin` is the superset and wins when both an exact-email entry and a wildcard-domain entry would match the same actor.\n\n`PEEK_ACCESS_POLICY` is a JSON array of `{ \"match\": \"...\", \"role\": \"business\" | \"admin\" }` entries:\n\n```json\n[\n  { \"match\": \"alice@example.com\",  \"role\": \"admin\" },\n  { \"match\": \"*@example.com\",       \"role\": \"business\" },\n  { \"match\": \"ops@partner.io\",      \"role\": \"business\" }\n]\n```\n\nRules:\n\n- `match` accepts an exact email or a `*@domain.tld` wildcard.\n- Matching is case-insensitive and trimmed.\n- An actor with no matching entry has no role → no page renders, no mutations run.\n- Route prefixes are guarded centrally: `/audit` requires `admin`; unknown route prefixes default to any resolved role (read-only). Update `PEEK_ROUTE_RULES` in the access-policy module to add new sensitive prefixes.\n- Mutation action ids fail closed: an action id without an entry in `PEEK_ACTION_RULES` is denied even for `admin`. Current registered ids: `kol_rate.update` (business+admin), `fraud_flag.status.update` (admin), `dogpile.cancel` (admin), `reward_config.update` (admin).\n- The admin shell hides nav links the actor cannot reach.\n\n## Local dev identity\n\nWhen `NODE_ENV=development`, the proxy honors `PEEK_DEV_ACCESS_EMAIL` and skips Cloudflare verification:\n\n```bash\nPEEK_DEV_ACCESS_EMAIL=dev@example.com\nPEEK_ACCESS_POLICY='[{\"match\":\"dev@example.com\",\"role\":\"admin\"}]'\n```\n\nThe bypass is ignored in production builds — `pnpm build` + production runtime always require a valid Cloudflare JWT.\n\n## Audit behavior (FR-11)\n\n`peek` writes to the existing `operator_events` table; no migration is owned by this app. All peek-emitted events are prefixed `peek.`:\n\n- `peek.search` — universal-search calls.\n- `peek.user.view_sensitive` — sensitive user-detail sections render.\n- `peek.export` — every CSV export, emitted **before** rows are returned.\n- `peek.access.denied` — access-denied attempts (when logged).\n- `peek.change.applied` — successful mutation, with before/after diff.\n- `peek.change.rejected` — denied / invalid / failed mutation attempts.\n\nEvery payload includes the actor email, route, action id, resource type/id, filter summary, result count, and request id. Secrets (JWTs, DB URLs, private keys, raw passwords/tokens) are redacted by `peek/src/server/audit/redact.ts` before insert. Audit insert failures do not leak data to the browser; the caller handles failure as a denial.\n\n## Exports (FR-12)\n\nServer-side CSV exports under `peek/src/server/exports/**`:\n\n- Each export targets a filtered table — full-table dumps are rejected with `no_filters`.\n- Each export has a per-entity row cap, bounded by `PEEK_EXPORT_ROW_CAP_DEFAULT` (`5000`).\n- Filenames are deterministic: `<entity>-<yyyy-mm-dd>-<filter-slug>.csv`.\n- A `peek.export` audit event is emitted before any rows are returned. If audit emission fails, the export is refused (`audit_emit_failed`).\n- In production, exports are disabled when audit logging is not configured (no `DATABASE_URL`).\n- Export routes inherit the page-level access of the source page; UI export actions hide for actors that cannot read the page.\n\n## Mutation rules (FR-14)\n\nAll business-state writes live under `peek/src/server/mutations/**`. Each definition declares:\n\n- A stable action id registered in `PEEK_ACTION_RULES` (otherwise the runner denies with `unauthorized`).\n- A `resourceType` recorded on the audit event.\n- A `zod` input schema; invalid input is rejected with `peek.change.rejected`.\n- An `execute` callback that runs inside a `sql.begin(...)` transaction so the mutation and its audit insert commit (or roll back) atomically.\n\nApproved mutation candidates for this spec:\n\n- `kol_rate.update` — create/update a row in `referral_kol_rates`.\n- `fraud_flag.status.update` — transition a `fraud_flags.status` value through the allowed-transition matrix.\n- `dogpile.cancel` — cancel a future scheduled `dogpile_events` row (rejects active/ended/cancelled).\n- `reward_config.update` — edit one allowlisted `reward_config` key, gated by an explicit confirmation flag and a no-op-value guard.\n\nOut of scope until a future spec adds acceptance criteria: queue retry/replay, claim payout overrides, crate payout overrides, profile identity edits, transaction edits, and settlement edits. Direct DB writes from `peek` outside the approved mutations and the `operator_events` audit insert are not allowed.\n\n## Commands\n\n- `pnpm dev`\n- `pnpm build`\n- `pnpm start`\n- `pnpm typecheck`\n- `pnpm test`\n- `pnpm test:e2e`\n- `pnpm verify` — lint, typecheck, test, and production build (run before commits/PRs).\n\n`peek` is server-rendered Postgres reads + scoped DB writes only; it has no on-chain, oracle, or VRF integration, so devnet E2E coverage does not apply. Run the root `./scripts/verify` if a change is cross-repo or before a release-tagged PR; this spec introduces no public backend API or OpenAPI changes.\n\n## Deploy\n\n`peek` deploys separate dev and production App Platform apps. Pushes to `dev` deploy the dev app from `.do/app-dev.yaml`; version tags matching `v*.*.*` deploy production from `.do/app-prod.yaml`. See `.do/README.md` for the current DigitalOcean and GitHub deployment model.\n\nThe deployed environment must set `DATABASE_URL`, `CF_ACCESS_TEAM_DOMAIN`, `CF_ACCESS_AUD`, and `PEEK_ACCESS_POLICY` (otherwise no actor resolves to a role and every page renders the access-denied panel).\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":568,"cache_read_input_tokens":90376,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":568},"output_tokens":41,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fbb345f7-d650-4fa3-be65-355d8ff344be","uuid":"ccfdfd24-b0f7-4b4a-9c58-5eb72d6ac90b"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GUftPAkAf4MpJCmqmoXo98","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /workspaces/rng-utopia/peek/README.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fbb345f7-d650-4fa3-be65-355d8ff344be","uuid":"dde19333-52d2-4674-9912-dc56b673476b","timestamp":"2026-04-26T20:03:02.418Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"update","filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/peek/README.md","content":"# Peek\n\nInternal operations admin for Taunt Bet — users, growth/referrals, games, economy (rewards/points/crates/challenges), queue, dogpile, fraud review, audit, and exports — built on Next.js App Router with server-only Postgres reads and a small set of audited admin mutations.\n\nUses **pnpm** (pinned in `package.json` `packageManager`). Non-frontend service repos in this org standardize on pnpm.\n\n## Setup\n\n```bash\npnpm install\ncp .env.example .env.local\npnpm dev\n```\n\n## Required env\n\n- `DATABASE_URL`\n- `CF_ACCESS_TEAM_DOMAIN` — Cloudflare Access team domain, e.g. `https://team.cloudflareaccess.com`\n- `CF_ACCESS_AUD` — Cloudflare Access application audience tag\n\n## Optional env\n\n- `PEEK_ACCESS_POLICY` — JSON array mapping verified Cloudflare emails/domains to local roles. See \"Local roles\" below.\n- `PEEK_DEV_ACCESS_EMAIL` — local-only Cloudflare Access bypass; honored only when `NODE_ENV=development`. See \"Local dev identity\" below.\n- `PEEK_DEFAULT_PAGE_SIZE` — defaults to `50` if unset.\n- `PEEK_DB_CONNECT_TIMEOUT_SECONDS` — defaults to `5` so the UI fails fast when the database is unreachable.\n\n## Cloudflare Access (jose)\n\nCloudflare Zero Trust Access is the outer identity gate. `peek` does **not** maintain a second global email allowlist for base access — Cloudflare decides who can reach the app.\n\nThe proxy (`peek/proxy.ts`) verifies the `cf-access-jwt-assertion` header on every request using [`jose`](https://github.com/panva/jose):\n\n- `createRemoteJWKSet(${CF_ACCESS_TEAM_DOMAIN}/cdn-cgi/access/certs)` fetches and caches the signing keys.\n- `jwtVerify(...)` validates signature, `algorithms: [\"RS256\"]`, `issuer = CF_ACCESS_TEAM_DOMAIN`, `audience = CF_ACCESS_AUD`, and expiration.\n- The verified `email` claim is normalized (trimmed + lowercased), then forwarded as the trusted server-only `x-peek-verified-access-email` header. Any browser-supplied copy of that header is stripped before any downstream code runs.\n- A request without a valid JWT receives `403 Cloudflare Access required`. A request with a valid JWT but missing `email` claim is denied at render time by the role resolver (no role → access-denied panel).\n\nCustom JWKS / signature code has been removed; production correctness depends on `jose`'s validation.\n\n## Local roles (FR-2)\n\nA valid Cloudflare JWT proves identity. App authorization is decided locally in `peek/src/server/access-policy.ts`, keyed off the verified email.\n\nRoles: `business` and `admin`. `admin` is the superset and wins when both an exact-email entry and a wildcard-domain entry would match the same actor.\n\n`PEEK_ACCESS_POLICY` is a JSON array of `{ \"match\": \"...\", \"role\": \"business\" | \"admin\" }` entries:\n\n```json\n[\n  { \"match\": \"alice@example.com\",  \"role\": \"admin\" },\n  { \"match\": \"*@example.com\",       \"role\": \"business\" },\n  { \"match\": \"ops@partner.io\",      \"role\": \"business\" }\n]\n```\n\nRules:\n\n- `match` accepts an exact email or a `*@domain.tld` wildcard.\n- Matching is case-insensitive and trimmed.\n- An actor with no matching entry has no role → no page renders, no mutations run.\n- Route prefixes are guarded centrally: `/audit` requires `admin`; unknown route prefixes default to any resolved role (read-only). Update `PEEK_ROUTE_RULES` in the access-policy module to add new sensitive prefixes.\n- Mutation action ids fail closed: an action id without an entry in `PEEK_ACTION_RULES` is denied even for `admin`. Current registered ids: `kol_rate.update` (business+admin), `fraud_flag.status.update` (admin), `dogpile.cancel` (admin), `reward_config.update` (admin).\n- The admin shell hides nav links the actor cannot reach.\n\n## Local dev identity\n\nWhen `NODE_ENV=development`, the proxy honors `PEEK_DEV_ACCESS_EMAIL` and skips Cloudflare verification:\n\n```bash\nPEEK_DEV_ACCESS_EMAIL=dev@example.com\nPEEK_ACCESS_POLICY='[{\"match\":\"dev@example.com\",\"role\":\"admin\"}]'\n```\n\nThe bypass is ignored in production builds — `pnpm build` + production runtime always require a valid Cloudflare JWT.\n\n## Audit behavior (FR-11)\n\n`peek` writes to the existing `operator_events` table; no migration is owned by this app. All peek-emitted events are prefixed `peek.`:\n\n- `peek.search` — universal-search calls.\n- `peek.user.view_sensitive` — sensitive user-detail sections render.\n- `peek.export` — every CSV export, emitted **before** rows are returned.\n- `peek.access.denied` — access-denied attempts (when logged).\n- `peek.change.applied` — successful mutation, with before/after diff.\n- `peek.change.rejected` — denied / invalid / failed mutation attempts.\n\nEvery payload includes the actor email, route, action id, resource type/id, filter summary, result count, and request id. Secrets (JWTs, DB URLs, private keys, raw passwords/tokens) are redacted by `peek/src/server/audit/redact.ts` before insert. Audit insert failures do not leak data to the browser; the caller handles failure as a denial.\n\n## Exports (FR-12)\n\nServer-side CSV exports under `peek/src/server/exports/**`:\n\n- Each export targets a filtered table — full-table dumps are rejected with `no_filters`.\n- Each export has a per-entity row cap, bounded by `PEEK_EXPORT_ROW_CAP_DEFAULT` (`5000`).\n- Filenames are deterministic: `<entity>-<yyyy-mm-dd>-<filter-slug>.csv`.\n- A `peek.export` audit event is emitted before any rows are returned. If audit emission fails, the export is refused (`audit_emit_failed`).\n- In production, exports are disabled when audit logging is not configured (no `DATABASE_URL`).\n- Export routes inherit the page-level access of the source page; UI export actions hide for actors that cannot read the page.\n\n## Mutation rules (FR-14)\n\nAll business-state writes live under `peek/src/server/mutations/**`. Each definition declares:\n\n- A stable action id registered in `PEEK_ACTION_RULES` (otherwise the runner denies with `unauthorized`).\n- A `resourceType` recorded on the audit event.\n- A `zod` input schema; invalid input is rejected with `peek.change.rejected`.\n- An `execute` callback that runs inside a `sql.begin(...)` transaction so the mutation and its audit insert commit (or roll back) atomically.\n\nApproved mutation candidates for this spec:\n\n- `kol_rate.update` — create/update a row in `referral_kol_rates`.\n- `fraud_flag.status.update` — transition a `fraud_flags.status` value through the allowed-transition matrix.\n- `dogpile.cancel` — cancel a future scheduled `dogpile_events` row (rejects active/ended/cancelled).\n- `reward_config.update` — edit one allowlisted `reward_config` key, gated by an explicit confirmation flag and a no-op-value guard.\n\nOut of scope until a future spec adds acceptance criteria: queue retry/replay, claim payout overrides, crate payout overrides, profile identity edits, transaction edits, and settlement edits. Direct DB writes from `peek` outside the approved mutations and the `operator_events` audit insert are not allowed.\n\n## Commands\n\n- `pnpm dev`\n- `pnpm build`\n- `pnpm start`\n- `pnpm typecheck`\n- `pnpm test`\n- `pnpm test:e2e`\n- `pnpm verify` — lint, typecheck, test, and production build (run before commits/PRs).\n\n`peek` is server-rendered Postgres reads + scoped DB writes only; it has no on-chain, oracle, or VRF integration, so devnet E2E coverage does not apply. Run the root `./scripts/verify` if a change is cross-repo or before a release-tagged PR; this spec introduces no public backend API or OpenAPI changes.\n\n## Deploy\n\n`peek` deploys separate dev and production App Platform apps. Pushes to `dev` deploy the dev app from `.do/app-dev.yaml`; version tags matching `v*.*.*` deploy production from `.do/app-prod.yaml`. See `.do/README.md` for the current DigitalOcean and GitHub deployment model.\n\nThe deployed environment must set `DATABASE_URL`, `CF_ACCESS_TEAM_DOMAIN`, `CF_ACCESS_AUD`, and `PEEK_ACCESS_POLICY` (otherwise no actor resolves to a role and every page renders the access-denied panel).\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":1,"oldLines":6,"newStart":1,"newLines":6,"lines":[" # Peek"," ","-Internal waitlist and referral admin for Taunt Bet.","+Internal operations admin for Taunt Bet — users, growth/referrals, games, economy (rewards/points/crates/challenges), queue, dogpile, fraud review, audit, and exports — built on Next.js App Router with server-only Postgres reads and a small set of audited admin mutations."," "," Uses **pnpm** (pinned in `package.json` `packageManager`). Non-frontend service repos in this org standardize on pnpm."," "]},{"oldStart":18,"oldLines":11,"newStart":18,"newLines":104,"lines":[" - `CF_ACCESS_TEAM_DOMAIN` — Cloudflare Access team domain, e.g. `https://team.cloudflareaccess.com`"," - `CF_ACCESS_AUD` — Cloudflare Access application audience tag"," ","-Optional:","+## Optional env"," ","-- `PEEK_DEFAULT_PAGE_SIZE` — defaults to `50` if unset","-- `PEEK_DB_CONNECT_TIMEOUT_SECONDS` — defaults to `5` so the UI fails fast when the database is unreachable","+- `PEEK_ACCESS_POLICY` — JSON array mapping verified Cloudflare emails/domains to local roles. See \"Local roles\" below.","+- `PEEK_DEV_ACCESS_EMAIL` — local-only Cloudflare Access bypass; honored only when `NODE_ENV=development`. See \"Local dev identity\" below.","+- `PEEK_DEFAULT_PAGE_SIZE` — defaults to `50` if unset.","+- `PEEK_DB_CONNECT_TIMEOUT_SECONDS` — defaults to `5` so the UI fails fast when the database is unreachable."," ","+## Cloudflare Access (jose)","+","+Cloudflare Zero Trust 