erver/exports/**`:","+","+- Each export targets a filtered table — full-table dumps are rejected with `no_filters`.","+- Each export has a per-entity row cap, bounded by `PEEK_EXPORT_ROW_CAP_DEFAULT` (`5000`).","+- Filenames are deterministic: `<entity>-<yyyy-mm-dd>-<filter-slug>.csv`.","+- A `peek.export` audit event is emitted before any rows are returned. If audit emission fails, the export is refused (`audit_emit_failed`).","+- In production, exports are disabled when audit logging is not configured (no `DATABASE_URL`).","+- Export routes inherit the page-level access of the source page; UI export actions hide for actors that cannot read the page.","+","+## Mutation rules (FR-14)","+","+All business-state writes live under `peek/src/server/mutations/**`. Each definition declares:","+","+- A stable action id registered in `PEEK_ACTION_RULES` (otherwise the runner denies with `unauthorized`).","+- A `resourceType` recorded on the audit event.","+- A `zod` input schema; invalid input is rejected with `peek.change.rejected`.","+- An `execute` callback that runs inside a `sql.begin(...)` transaction so the mutation and its audit insert commit (or roll back) atomically.","+","+Approved mutation candidates for this spec:","+","+- `kol_rate.update` — create/update a row in `referral_kol_rates`.","+- `fraud_flag.status.update` — transition a `fraud_flags.status` value through the allowed-transition matrix.","+- `dogpile.cancel` — cancel a future scheduled `dogpile_events` row (rejects active/ended/cancelled).","+- `reward_config.update` — edit one allowlisted `reward_config` key, gated by an explicit confirmation flag and a no-op-value guard.","+","+Out of scope until a future spec adds acceptance criteria: queue retry/replay, claim payout overrides, crate payout overrides, profile identity edits, transaction edits, and settlement edits. Direct DB writes from `peek` outside the approved mutations and the `operator_events` audit insert are not allowed.","+"," ## Commands"," "," - `pnpm dev`"]},{"oldStart":31,"oldLines":8,"newStart":124,"newLines":12,"lines":[" - `pnpm typecheck`"," - `pnpm test`"," - `pnpm test:e2e`","-- `pnpm verify` — lint, typecheck, test, and production build","+- `pnpm verify` — lint, typecheck, test, and production build (run before commits/PRs)."," ","+`peek` is server-rendered Postgres reads + scoped DB writes only; it has no on-chain, oracle, or VRF integration, so devnet E2E coverage does not apply. Run the root `./scripts/verify` if a change is cross-repo or before a release-tagged PR; this spec introduces no public backend API or OpenAPI changes.","+"," ## Deploy"," "," `peek` deploys separate dev and production App Platform apps. Pushes to `dev` deploy the dev app from `.do/app-dev.yaml`; version tags matching `v*.*.*` deploy production from `.do/app-prod.yaml`. See `.do/README.md` for the current DigitalOcean and GitHub deployment model.","+","+The deployed environment must set `DATABASE_URL`, `CF_ACCESS_TEAM_DOMAIN`, `CF_ACCESS_AUD`, and `PEEK_ACCESS_POLICY` (otherwise no actor resolves to a role and every page renders the access-denied panel)."]}],"originalFile":"# Peek\n\nInternal waitlist and referral admin for Taunt Bet.\n\nUses **pnpm** (pinned in `package.json` `packageManager`). Non-frontend service repos in this org standardize on pnpm.\n\n## Setup\n\n```bash\npnpm install\ncp .env.example .env.local\npnpm dev\n```\n\n## Required env\n\n- `DATABASE_URL`\n- `CF_ACCESS_TEAM_DOMAIN` — Cloudflare Access team domain, e.g. `https://team.cloudflareaccess.com`\n- `CF_ACCESS_AUD` — Cloudflare Access application audience tag\n\nOptional:\n\n- `PEEK_DEFAULT_PAGE_SIZE` — defaults to `50` if unset\n- `PEEK_DB_CONNECT_TIMEOUT_SECONDS` — defaults to `5` so the UI fails fast when the database is unreachable\n\n## Commands\n\n- `pnpm dev`\n- `pnpm build`\n- `pnpm start`\n- `pnpm typecheck`\n- `pnpm test`\n- `pnpm test:e2e`\n- `pnpm verify` — lint, typecheck, test, and production build\n\n## Deploy\n\n`peek` deploys separate dev and production App Platform apps. Pushes to `dev` deploy the dev app from `.do/app-dev.yaml`; version tags matching `v*.*.*` deploy production from `.do/app-prod.yaml`. See `.do/README.md` for the current DigitalOcean and GitHub deployment model.\n","userModified":false}}
